Advanced C Programming – Important Questions
## Introduction

This section contains important advanced-level C programming problems that are frequently asked in interviews and coding tests. These questions focus on arrays, pointers, functions, and algorithmic thinking to build strong problem-solving skills.

## Topics Covered

Arrays and searching techniques
Pointer manipulation
Functions and modular design
Mathematical logic problems
In-place array operations
Optimization-based thinking

## Problem Statements (7 Important Advanced Questions)

1) Find All Prime Numbers up to N (Optimized)

Write a program to print all prime numbers from 1 to N using an optimized function (check only up to √n).

2) Second Largest Element (Without Sorting)

Find the second largest element in an array in a single traversal.

3) Array Rotation (Left Rotation by K steps) ⭐

Rotate an array to the left by K positions without using extra array (in-place logic preferred).

4) Palindrome Number Check using Function

Check whether a number is palindrome using a reusable function.

5) GCD and LCM using Euclidean Algorithm

Find GCD and LCM using optimized Euclidean algorithm (function-based).

6) Frequency Count in Array (Optimized Approach)

Count frequency of elements using nested loops (no hash/map).

7) Pointer-Based Array Update + Swap Logic

Use pointers to:

Swap two variables
Modify array elements using pointer arithmetic
